as="geometry" /> </mxCell> <mxCell id="pNnbbz1IgtCxc-YyWr1T-31" value="<font style="font-size: 14px;" color="#000000"><b>NOTES:</b><br><br>1. Customer might want to monitor resources on multiple accounts (they are called "Monitored AWS Accounts") while deploying AlertsMon solution only once (on "Tooling AWS Account")<br><br>2. Tooling and one of monitored account can be the same. Separation is not obligatory.<br><br><b>FLOWS</b>:<br>1. <b>Notifications flow </b>- e.g. send e-mail immediately after Glue Job fails. Not necessary failure. Some might require notification on successful completion.<br>Main ideas of the flow: 1) Event-based with Granular event (e.g. Athena query failed), 2) Initiated inside Monitored account, 3) Pushes event to Tooling account as tooling knows (from Settings) what to do with the event (should we sent a notification for it and if "yes" - to whom)<br><br>2. <b>Monitoring flow </b>- centralize RELEVANT monitoring-related data and stores inside storage in "Tooling account". It's executed once in &lt;x&gt; minutes, depending on Settings. Too often - overhead &amp; cost, too rare - dashboards will lag behind for &lt;x&gt; minutes.<br>Data extraction examples:<br>- boto3 Glue client: method "get_glue_job_runs" (since previous data extraction)<br>- lambda: cloudwatch logs extracts (again since last update)<br><br><b>Components</b>:<br>- "Settings component" - Stores config about monitored resources and alerts/digest subscribers. In details described in another tab of this files.<br><br>- "Notification service" - Responsible for sending out notifications (no business logic, just transport). Implementation depends on config - uses AWS SES under the hood, or existing company's SMTP server. Can be expanded later (?push notifications).<br><br>- "Monitoring Data Extraction Component" - uses Boto3 methods to retrieve data from Monitored accounts (from CloudWatch data, from specific service APIs etc.). Executed once in &lt;x&gt; minutes - from "Settings". Stores in "Metrics Data Storage".<br>Time-series DB to feed Grafana dashboards?<br><br>- "Interactive Dashboards" - self-explanatory :) Expecting something like Grafana<br><br><br></font>" Tooling and one of monitored account can be the same. Separation is not obligatory.<br><br><b>FLOWS</b>:<br>1. <b>Notifications flow </b>- e.g. send e-mail immediately after Glue Job fails. Not necessary failure. Some might require notification on successful completion.<br>Main ideas of the flow: 1) Event-based with Granular event (e.g. Athena query failed), 2) Initiated inside Monitored account, 3) Pushes event to Tooling account as tooling knows (from Settings) what to do with the event (should we sent a notification for it and if "yes" - to whom)<br><br>2. <b>Monitoring flow </b>- centralize RELEVANT monitoring-related data and stores inside storage in "Tooling account". It's executed once in &lt;x&gt; minutes, depending on Settings. Too often - overhead &amp; cost, too rare - dashboards will lag behind for &lt;x&gt; minutes.<br>Data extraction examples:<br>- boto3 Glue client: method "get_glue_job_runs" (since previous data extraction)<br>- lambda: cloudwatch logs extracts (again since last update)<br><br><b>Components</b>:<br>- "Settings component" - Stores config about monitored resources and alerts/digest subscribers. In details described in another tab of this files.<br><br>- "Notification service" - Responsible for sending out notifications (no business logic, just transport). <br>SQS receives event (alerts/digest) payload, triggers lambda function which parses payload and formats it according to delivery method mentioned in payload, then, uses delivery method (AWS SES / SMTP / Slack / Teams) to send the message to recipient.<br>* - example alert and digest payload - see a separate tab<br><br>- "Monitoring Data Extraction Component" - uses Boto3 methods to retrieve data from Monitored accounts (from CloudWatch data, from specific service APIs etc.). Executed once in &lt;x&gt; minutes - from "Settings". <mxCell id="CxA6B_-6gKKxICvClZ7t-5" value="<font style="font-size: 14px;" color="#000000"><b>NOTES:</b><br><br>1. Customer might want to monitor resources on multiple accounts (they are called "Monitored AWS Accounts") while deploying AlertsMon solution only once (on "Tooling AWS Account")<br><br>2. Tooling and one of monitored account can be the same. Separation is not obligatory.<br><br><b>FLOWS</b>:<br>1. <b>Notifications flow </b>- e.g. send e-mail immediately after Glue Job fails. Not necessary failure. Some might require notification on successful completion.<br>Main ideas of the flow: 1) Event-based with Granular event (e.g. Athena query failed), 2) Initiated inside Monitored account, 3) Pushes event to Tooling account as tooling knows (from Settings) what to do with the event (should we sent a notification for it and if "yes" - to whom)<br><br>2. <b>Monitoring flow </b>- centralize RELEVANT monitoring-related data and stores inside storage in "Tooling account". It's executed once in &lt;x&gt; minutes, depending on Settings. Too often - overhead &amp; cost, too rare - dashboards will lag behind for &lt;x&gt; minutes.<br>Data extraction examples:<br>- boto3 Glue client: method "get_glue_job_runs" (since previous data extraction)<br>- lambda: cloudwatch logs extracts (again since last update)<br><br><b>Components</b>:<br>- "Settings component" - Stores config about monitored resources and alerts/digest subscribers. In details described in another tab of this files.<br><br>- "Notification service" - Responsible for sending out notifications (no business logic, just transport). Implementation depends on config - uses AWS SES under the hood, or existing company's SMTP server. Can be expanded later (?push notifications).<br><br>- "Monitoring Data Extraction Component" - uses Boto3 methods to retrieve data from Monitored accounts (from CloudWatch data, from specific service APIs etc.). Executed once in &lt;x&gt; minutes - from "Settings".
